<section id="fs-id1167791543265" class="key-concepts">
<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list id="fs-id1167791543272" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet">
<item>Several physical applications of the definite integral are common in engineering and physics.</item>
<item>Definite integrals can be used to determine the mass of an object if its density function is known.</item>
<item>Work can also be calculated from integrating a force function, or when counteracting the force of gravity, as in a pumping problem.</item>
<item>Definite integrals can also be used to calculate the force exerted on an object submerged in a liquid.</item>
</list>
</section>
